<note type="curatorial">N. Center Copy St. Archives also has a copy</note>



<fw type="letterhead">
<hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT</hi>
<lb/>
<hi rend="caps">ROUTE 7 SKYRIM FARM</hi>
<lb/>
<hi rend="caps">COLUMBIA, MISSOURI</hi>  
</fw>
<fw type="curatorial">16</fw>
<opener>
<dateline>Nov. 16, '64</dateline>


<salute>Dear Mrs. Anderson:</salute>
</opener>
<p>I was very glad indeed to hear from you, and I thank you for the copy of the article about our mutual friend, Dr. J. T. House. I have the article among my papers, but have not seen it for a long while. Dr. never made the trip because, as I remember, his wife had a bad sick spell that summer and he could not get away. I'm sure he could have done it.</p>
 
<p><hi rend="underline">The River and I</hi> is out of print now, but no doubt it will be reissued in a year or two. It should 

<note type="authorial">(over)</note>

<note type="authorial">The date, I believe was 1916, possibly 1917.</note>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.44.16-17_0002"/>
<fw type="curatorial">17</fw>

be in all large libraries; and large second-hand bookstores can often locate copies at a premium &#8212; It is a collector's item, but is priced generally below $10.</p>

<p>I wish I could have another drink from your Fountain of Youth!!</p>

<p>Do give my kindest thoughts to your Father, and retain a goodly supply of them for yourself.</p>
<closer>
<salute>Sincerely,</salute>

<signed>John Neihardt</signed>
</closer>
</div1>
